WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.170 align:middle line:90%


00:00:07.170 --> 00:00:09.616 align:middle line:84%
>>Everyone's fond of
saying that coastlines,

00:00:09.616 --> 00:00:14.480 align:middle line:84%
and some forest distributions,
and all this stuff are fractal.

00:00:14.480 --> 00:00:19.330 align:middle line:84%
Well, doesn't this imply that
there is then a global fractal?

00:00:19.330 --> 00:00:21.680 align:middle line:84%
There is a fractal
dimension, which,

00:00:21.680 --> 00:00:23.670 align:middle line:84%
when you feed it
into your computer,

00:00:23.670 --> 00:00:26.920 align:middle line:84%
and wrap the data
around a sphere,

00:00:26.920 --> 00:00:31.700 align:middle line:84%
the continents and oceans
of Earth should appear.

00:00:31.700 --> 00:00:36.070 align:middle line:84%
And in principle, again
to the absurd level,

00:00:36.070 --> 00:00:38.450 align:middle line:84%
you should be able
to then telescope

00:00:38.450 --> 00:00:40.865 align:middle line:84%
in on that portion
of this data that

00:00:40.865 --> 00:00:44.490 align:middle line:84%
is wrapped around the sphere
that corresponds to the North

00:00:44.490 --> 00:00:47.920 align:middle line:84%
California, and on
your computer screen

00:00:47.920 --> 00:00:52.420 align:middle line:84%
should appear Esalen hung
on the cliffs of Big Sur,

00:00:52.420 --> 00:00:56.920 align:middle line:84%
with us sitting in a room
inside, discussing the matter.

00:00:56.920 --> 00:01:00.300 align:middle line:90%
>>Rupert, Terence, I'm Ralph.

00:01:00.300 --> 00:01:05.072 align:middle line:84%
Creation, imagination--
my mask is chaos.

00:01:05.072 --> 00:01:55.960 align:middle line:90%


00:01:55.960 --> 00:02:00.280 align:middle line:10%
>>In my early LSD
experiences, I seemed

00:02:00.280 --> 00:02:05.540 align:middle line:10%
to see motifs and
structures that

00:02:05.540 --> 00:02:10.530 align:middle line:10%
gave me an interest
in Tibetan Buddhism.

00:02:10.530 --> 00:02:15.190 align:middle line:10%
And I went to India with the
intent of studying the Tibetan

00:02:15.190 --> 00:02:18.870 align:middle line:10%
language, and quickly found
that the whole thing was

00:02:18.870 --> 00:02:22.160 align:middle line:10%
just overwhelming,
and that I was just

00:02:22.160 --> 00:02:25.560 align:middle line:10%
a human atom in
the sea of India,

00:02:25.560 --> 00:02:30.230 align:middle line:10%
and that the notion of
encompassing or understanding

00:02:30.230 --> 00:02:35.750 align:middle line:10%
what this was, was clearly
the task of a lifetime.

00:02:35.750 --> 00:02:38.960 align:middle line:10%
And several times in my
life, I have acted out

00:02:38.960 --> 00:02:42.790 align:middle line:10%
this sort of
ricocheting relationship

00:02:42.790 --> 00:02:49.670 align:middle line:10%
between the humanities and
the sciences, at times,

00:02:49.670 --> 00:02:54.600 align:middle line:10%
losing myself in the study
of certain schools of poetry,

00:02:54.600 --> 00:02:58.430 align:middle line:10%
or literature, or painting,
and then, at other times,

00:02:58.430 --> 00:03:02.220 align:middle line:10%
spending years reading
the philosophy of science,

00:03:02.220 --> 00:03:07.410 align:middle line:10%
and epistemic basis of physics,
and this sort of thing,

00:03:07.410 --> 00:03:14.440 align:middle line:10%
always trying to get a
resolution on the content

00:03:14.440 --> 00:03:20.590 align:middle line:10%
of my experience, my lived
experience, which included

00:03:20.590 --> 00:03:25.190 align:middle line:10%
the psychedelic experience,
which for me, from very

00:03:25.190 --> 00:03:32.390 align:middle line:10%
early on, was this tremendous
mystery or conundrum, which

00:03:32.390 --> 00:03:35.890 align:middle line:10%
was set down in the
middle of my being.

00:03:35.890 --> 00:03:37.660 align:middle line:84%
And it still
continues like that.

00:03:37.660 --> 00:03:43.260 align:middle line:84%
I keep returning to that,
testing all the ideas

00:03:43.260 --> 00:03:47.855 align:middle line:84%
against the fullness
of experience.

00:03:47.855 --> 00:03:57.370 align:middle line:90%


00:03:57.370 --> 00:04:01.310 align:middle line:84%
The main difference between
our world and the world

00:04:01.310 --> 00:04:03.930 align:middle line:84%
that science tells
us we're living in

00:04:03.930 --> 00:04:10.900 align:middle line:84%
is that science denies the
quirky, freaky, cosmic giggle,

00:04:10.900 --> 00:04:14.630 align:middle line:84%
high plottedness,
completely improbable,

00:04:14.630 --> 00:04:20.360 align:middle line:84%
totally quirky humor that
binds everything together,

00:04:20.360 --> 00:04:21.820 align:middle line:84%
and that makes it
something other

00:04:21.820 --> 00:04:25.960 align:middle line:84%
than an engine in which
atoms blindly run,

00:04:25.960 --> 00:04:28.020 align:middle line:90%
in Whitehead's phrase.

00:04:28.020 --> 00:04:31.470 align:middle line:84%
Schrodinger
brilliantly anticipated

00:04:31.470 --> 00:04:36.650 align:middle line:84%
the discovery of DNA, and then
Joseph Needham and LL White.

00:04:36.650 --> 00:04:41.100 align:middle line:84%
And Erich Jantsch should
be mentioned, actually,

00:04:41.100 --> 00:04:44.555 align:middle line:84%
as a precursor of
us all, I think.

00:04:44.555 --> 00:04:48.600 align:middle line:84%
I mean, Erich Jantsch was a
great pioneer, a great soul.

00:04:48.600 --> 00:04:52.490 align:middle line:10%
And he saw very deeply
into whole systems,

00:04:52.490 --> 00:04:56.720 align:middle line:10%
as did Ilya Prigogine, the
Belgian thermodynamicist.

00:04:56.720 --> 00:05:01.430 align:middle line:84%
And I think a lot of all of what
we're doing comes out of that.

00:05:01.430 --> 00:05:04.800 align:middle line:84%
What Prigogine showed
that just brought down

00:05:04.800 --> 00:05:10.540 align:middle line:84%
the house was that there
could be perturbations

00:05:10.540 --> 00:05:14.830 align:middle line:84%
of physical systems
that were unpredictable,

00:05:14.830 --> 00:05:19.330 align:middle line:84%
and that would cause the
whole system to actually move

00:05:19.330 --> 00:05:24.300 align:middle line:84%
to a more ordered state
than the initial state.

00:05:24.300 --> 00:05:27.800 align:middle line:84%
And this perturbation to
higher states of order

00:05:27.800 --> 00:05:30.320 align:middle line:84%
looks suspiciously
like a violation

00:05:30.320 --> 00:05:35.430 align:middle line:84%
of the supposedly inviolate
Second Law of Thermodynamics.

00:05:35.430 --> 00:05:40.945 align:middle line:84%
So that looks like a doorway
into an energetic hyperspace.

00:05:40.945 --> 00:05:49.890 align:middle line:90%


00:05:49.890 --> 00:05:53.000 align:middle line:10%
>>Well, when "A New
Science of Life"

00:05:53.000 --> 00:05:55.640 align:middle line:10%
came out in 1982 in
America-- it came out

00:05:55.640 --> 00:05:59.370 align:middle line:10%
a year earlier in England-- I
came to California, because it

00:05:59.370 --> 00:06:01.580 align:middle line:10%
was published in Los Angeles.

00:06:01.580 --> 00:06:03.520 align:middle line:90%
I found myself here at Esalen.

00:06:03.520 --> 00:06:06.990 align:middle line:84%
I found an extraordinary new
range of things going on I

00:06:06.990 --> 00:06:08.510 align:middle line:90%
hadn't known about.

00:06:08.510 --> 00:06:13.690 align:middle line:84%
And when I was in San Francisco,
a friend who I knew from Europe

00:06:13.690 --> 00:06:17.120 align:middle line:84%
said to me just the day
before I left "there's

00:06:17.120 --> 00:06:19.120 align:middle line:90%
somebody you must meet.

00:06:19.120 --> 00:06:21.320 align:middle line:90%
He's called Terence McKenna."

00:06:21.320 --> 00:06:23.250 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know much
about Terence.

00:06:23.250 --> 00:06:29.390 align:middle line:84%
So I went up there, and,
in this large 1956 Buick,

00:06:29.390 --> 00:06:34.020 align:middle line:84%
we headed off into the
woods in Sonoma County,

00:06:34.020 --> 00:06:35.260 align:middle line:90%
where Terence lives.

00:06:35.260 --> 00:06:37.590 align:middle line:84%
And there I met both
Terence and Ralph,

00:06:37.590 --> 00:06:39.470 align:middle line:90%
who was there for the day.

00:06:39.470 --> 00:06:43.400 align:middle line:84%
I found that part of my
interest in these other realms

00:06:43.400 --> 00:06:45.780 align:middle line:84%
of reality, of course, like
many people in this room,

00:06:45.780 --> 00:06:50.140 align:middle line:84%
was stimulated by experience
with psychedelic substances.

00:06:50.140 --> 00:06:52.060 align:middle line:90%
This was before I went to India.

00:06:52.060 --> 00:06:54.200 align:middle line:84%
When I arrived in India,
I found that India

00:06:54.200 --> 00:06:57.000 align:middle line:84%
is a kind of psychedelic
realm, anyway.

00:06:57.000 --> 00:06:58.915 align:middle line:90%
It's just an amazing place.

00:06:58.915 --> 00:07:02.110 align:middle line:90%


00:07:02.110 --> 00:07:05.130 align:middle line:84%
So in Terence, I
found somebody who

00:07:05.130 --> 00:07:07.590 align:middle line:84%
knew about that whole
realm, who shared

00:07:07.590 --> 00:07:09.980 align:middle line:84%
with me an interest in
India, since it played

00:07:09.980 --> 00:07:12.550 align:middle line:84%
an important part
in his development,

00:07:12.550 --> 00:07:15.830 align:middle line:84%
and who have views about
the nature of reality, which

00:07:15.830 --> 00:07:18.700 align:middle line:84%
complemented my own in
an extraordinary way.

00:07:18.700 --> 00:07:22.090 align:middle line:84%
My own theory is about
memory, and habit in nature.

00:07:22.090 --> 00:07:23.980 align:middle line:84%
Terence, I found, had
developed a theory

00:07:23.980 --> 00:07:27.250 align:middle line:84%
about novelty and
creativity in nature,

00:07:27.250 --> 00:07:31.240 align:middle line:84%
a theory about the quality of
time and the creation process

00:07:31.240 --> 00:07:34.440 align:middle line:84%
as it is related to the
ongoing flux of events.

00:07:34.440 --> 00:07:36.950 align:middle line:90%


00:07:36.950 --> 00:07:41.800 align:middle line:84%
And Ralph had a kind of
mathematical theory, which

00:07:41.800 --> 00:07:45.210 align:middle line:84%
was just the kind of thing
that the view of nature

00:07:45.210 --> 00:07:48.460 align:middle line:84%
I was trying to develop needed--
the idea of nature being drawn

00:07:48.460 --> 00:07:51.760 align:middle line:84%
by goals, or attractors in
the mathematical science

00:07:51.760 --> 00:07:52.640 align:middle line:90%
of dynamics.

00:07:52.640 --> 00:07:56.430 align:middle line:84%
This is a model of the reality
being pulled from ahead

00:07:56.430 --> 00:07:58.830 align:middle line:90%
by things called attractors.

00:07:58.830 --> 00:08:01.400 align:middle line:84%
It's a teleological,
animistic view

00:08:01.400 --> 00:08:07.470 align:middle line:84%
of nature dressed up in the
guise of mathematical models,

00:08:07.470 --> 00:08:09.920 align:middle line:90%
which I found most fascinating.

00:08:09.920 --> 00:08:13.860 align:middle line:84%
And so, for me, the meeting
with Ralph and Terence

00:08:13.860 --> 00:08:15.970 align:middle line:84%
was a step further
towards seeing

00:08:15.970 --> 00:08:19.540 align:middle line:84%
how one could begin to dream
of a world in which nature was

00:08:19.540 --> 00:08:22.170 align:middle line:84%
seen as alive, in which
the imagination permeated

00:08:22.170 --> 00:08:26.650 align:middle line:84%
all reality, in which animals
and plants are seen as part

00:08:26.650 --> 00:08:33.010 align:middle line:84%
of the living texture, the
living components, the cells,

00:08:33.010 --> 00:08:36.460 align:middle line:84%
and the life of Gaia, and
Gaia in the life of the cosmos

00:08:36.460 --> 00:08:41.890 align:middle line:84%
as a whole, in fact, a view
of the world as alive, which

00:08:41.890 --> 00:08:44.282 align:middle line:84%
recalls, in some respects,
the old cosmologies

00:08:44.282 --> 00:08:46.740 align:middle line:84%
of the ancient world, where
the cosmos was seen as a living

00:08:46.740 --> 00:08:50.220 align:middle line:84%
organism, where they
thought of the whole cosmos

00:08:50.220 --> 00:08:53.270 align:middle line:84%
as having a soul, the
soul of the world--

00:08:53.270 --> 00:08:54.130 align:middle line:90%
the Anima Mundi.

00:08:54.130 --> 00:08:57.078 align:middle line:90%


00:08:57.078 --> 00:09:01.060 align:middle line:84%
So I was brought up
in the field of music,

00:09:01.060 --> 00:09:05.870 align:middle line:84%
but I was attracted
to mathematics early.

00:09:05.870 --> 00:09:10.640 align:middle line:84%
And when I was 14, I played
in the state symphony.

00:09:10.640 --> 00:09:12.960 align:middle line:10%
After that, I started
in mathematics,

00:09:12.960 --> 00:09:16.800 align:middle line:10%
and I became a professor
at Berkeley, when I was 23.

00:09:16.800 --> 00:09:19.540 align:middle line:84%
I had an easy way
in mathematics.

00:09:19.540 --> 00:09:24.080 align:middle line:84%
And way the system
works, the carpet

00:09:24.080 --> 00:09:26.816 align:middle line:90%
is unrolled in front of you.

00:09:26.816 --> 00:09:29.780 align:middle line:84%
You have a few choices, but
basically, before you even

00:09:29.780 --> 00:09:32.040 align:middle line:84%
know what's happening,
the carpet is unrolled,

00:09:32.040 --> 00:09:36.600 align:middle line:84%
and you're down the runnel
into whatever you can

00:09:36.600 --> 00:09:39.720 align:middle line:90%
do that's useful to the system.

00:09:39.720 --> 00:09:45.880 align:middle line:90%
In this process, I lost nature.

00:09:45.880 --> 00:09:49.980 align:middle line:84%
But there was a great gain,
because I love it out there.

00:09:49.980 --> 00:09:51.950 align:middle line:90%
I love to be off the planet.

00:09:51.950 --> 00:09:56.250 align:middle line:84%
I always did, and to this
day, I spend very little time

00:09:56.250 --> 00:09:59.040 align:middle line:90%
on planet Earth.

00:09:59.040 --> 00:10:01.360 align:middle line:90%
So it went on in this way.

00:10:01.360 --> 00:10:04.690 align:middle line:84%
And by 1967, I was a
professor at Princeton.

00:10:04.690 --> 00:10:07.440 align:middle line:84%
I had written three
books on mathematics

00:10:07.440 --> 00:10:09.070 align:middle line:84%
that you need a
microscope to read.

00:10:09.070 --> 00:10:11.930 align:middle line:90%


00:10:11.930 --> 00:10:15.130 align:middle line:84%
And I had been studying,
for a long while, chaos.

00:10:15.130 --> 00:10:16.730 align:middle line:84%
But we didn't call
it "chaos" then,

00:10:16.730 --> 00:10:20.620 align:middle line:84%
and we didn't see in it any
role in the natural world,

00:10:20.620 --> 00:10:23.740 align:middle line:84%
or in social transformation,
or in the evolution

00:10:23.740 --> 00:10:24.610 align:middle line:90%
of consciousness.

00:10:24.610 --> 00:10:28.110 align:middle line:84%
Because we didn't think
about anything out there.

00:10:28.110 --> 00:10:30.899 align:middle line:84%
So one day, after my third book
was done, and I was exhausted,

00:10:30.899 --> 00:10:32.440 align:middle line:84%
and I looked up,
and all the students

00:10:32.440 --> 00:10:35.130 align:middle line:84%
were out in the courtyard,
demonstrating about the Vietnam

00:10:35.130 --> 00:10:39.620 align:middle line:84%
War, and to open the university
to women students, and so on.

00:10:39.620 --> 00:10:41.830 align:middle line:90%
I said what exactly is going on?

00:10:41.830 --> 00:10:43.390 align:middle line:90%
Here, they said, take this.

00:10:43.390 --> 00:10:48.700 align:middle line:90%


00:10:48.700 --> 00:10:50.680 align:middle line:84%
And so like many
people in that year,

00:10:50.680 --> 00:10:56.400 align:middle line:84%
or around that time in 1967,
my career had a bifurcation.

00:10:56.400 --> 00:11:00.080 align:middle line:84%
So I went off the track
with psychedelics,

00:11:00.080 --> 00:11:02.490 align:middle line:84%
with meditation, but
especially with searching,

00:11:02.490 --> 00:11:03.630 align:middle line:90%
with trying everything.

00:11:03.630 --> 00:11:07.030 align:middle line:84%
And eventually, I was living
in a cave in the Himalayas.

00:11:07.030 --> 00:11:09.700 align:middle line:84%
And when I returned
to California,

00:11:09.700 --> 00:11:11.550 align:middle line:84%
I was standing on
a street corner

00:11:11.550 --> 00:11:14.460 align:middle line:90%
in Santa Cruz in white pajamas.

00:11:14.460 --> 00:11:17.990 align:middle line:84%
And a car stopped, and an old
friend from a previous lifetime

00:11:17.990 --> 00:11:20.660 align:middle line:84%
said "there's somebody
you have to meet.

00:11:20.660 --> 00:11:22.310 align:middle line:90%
Get in the car."

00:11:22.310 --> 00:11:23.400 align:middle line:90%
I had nothing to do.

00:11:23.400 --> 00:11:24.310 align:middle line:90%
It sounded OK.

00:11:24.310 --> 00:11:29.000 align:middle line:84%
And in that time, I believed
that everything goes perfectly.

00:11:29.000 --> 00:11:32.089 align:middle line:84%
You just go along with
the flow, as they said.

00:11:32.089 --> 00:11:33.880 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know it would
be a two hour drive.

00:11:33.880 --> 00:11:34.713 align:middle line:90%
So I got in the car.

00:11:34.713 --> 00:11:36.770 align:middle line:84%
There was the two hour
drive to Berkeley.

00:11:36.770 --> 00:11:38.830 align:middle line:84%
And I was literally
dumped out of the car

00:11:38.830 --> 00:11:41.460 align:middle line:90%
on Terence's front step.

00:11:41.460 --> 00:11:44.810 align:middle line:84%
I had never heard of
Terence at the time-- 1972.

00:11:44.810 --> 00:11:47.770 align:middle line:84%
And I went in, and
what happened then-- I

00:11:47.770 --> 00:11:49.370 align:middle line:84%
would still say
that although we've

00:11:49.370 --> 00:11:53.360 align:middle line:84%
had many wonderful talks,
and exciting, thrilling,

00:11:53.360 --> 00:11:55.930 align:middle line:84%
and nutritious times in
the meanwhile, that that

00:11:55.930 --> 00:11:58.730 align:middle line:90%
was quite a miraculous chat.

00:11:58.730 --> 00:12:02.830 align:middle line:84%
Many subjects came up-- how to
grow mushrooms, outer space.

00:12:02.830 --> 00:12:03.430 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:12:03.430 --> 00:12:06.521 align:middle line:84%
Anything you could think of
all passed by in the course

00:12:06.521 --> 00:12:07.270 align:middle line:90%
of an hour or two.

00:12:07.270 --> 00:12:11.880 align:middle line:10%
In this way, we became
friends, and this habit we had,

00:12:11.880 --> 00:12:14.490 align:middle line:10%
this activity that
we do-- I mean,

00:12:14.490 --> 00:12:16.770 align:middle line:10%
we never go for a hike
or something like that.

00:12:16.770 --> 00:12:20.190 align:middle line:90%
We sit in the evening, and talk.

00:12:20.190 --> 00:12:25.520 align:middle line:84%
About what happens is
synergistic, miraculous

00:12:25.520 --> 00:12:27.360 align:middle line:90%
growth-- evolutionary.

00:12:27.360 --> 00:12:32.050 align:middle line:84%
And in this
revitalization of my work,

00:12:32.050 --> 00:12:34.810 align:middle line:84%
and eventually the whole
field of mathematics,

00:12:34.810 --> 00:12:37.580 align:middle line:84%
my conversations with
Terence-- whereas I

00:12:37.580 --> 00:12:40.770 align:middle line:84%
think we thought of them
as just good fun-- did

00:12:40.770 --> 00:12:45.910 align:middle line:84%
have a really fundamental
influence on everything

00:12:45.910 --> 00:12:47.500 align:middle line:90%
I've done since.

00:12:47.500 --> 00:12:50.275 align:middle line:84%
So fun-- I would say
"fun" is insulting.

00:12:50.275 --> 00:12:53.170 align:middle line:84%
I mean "thrilling," because
of going to the edge,

00:12:53.170 --> 00:12:55.884 align:middle line:84%
going beyond the edge,
having company there,

00:12:55.884 --> 00:12:57.550 align:middle line:84%
finding things which
you can bring back,

00:12:57.550 --> 00:13:02.430 align:middle line:84%
and they work, and become part
of everything you're doing.

00:13:02.430 --> 00:13:06.770 align:middle line:84%
So it's opened up
these phenomena

00:13:06.770 --> 00:13:09.580 align:middle line:84%
characterized by chaotic,
irregular, that is to say,

00:13:09.580 --> 00:13:14.700 align:middle line:84%
not well ordered in
the previous paradigm

00:13:14.700 --> 00:13:16.636 align:middle line:90%
of space-time structure.

00:13:16.636 --> 00:13:22.780 align:middle line:10%
For example, relationships among
people, the states and change

00:13:22.780 --> 00:13:28.370 align:middle line:10%
of states of society, the
whole process of history,

00:13:28.370 --> 00:13:32.940 align:middle line:10%
the intuitive experience,
subjective experience

00:13:32.940 --> 00:13:35.210 align:middle line:10%
